summaries.short: Season One Finale. Tom learns of a silent-film family scandal; Monk goes missing at the beach; Ally pulls on Tom's heartstrings.
summaries.full: Season One Finale. On their last day in California, Bea, Monk and Pete hit the beach while Tom meets a cousin whose grandfather was a famous silent-movie cowboy star called Tumbleweed Tim. Later, Monk goes missing at the beach; Al and Kitty throw a farewell party for Tom--which leads to the discovery of some dark secrets...and a turning point in Tom's relationship with Ally.

summaries.short: With the help of an American Indian chief and shaman, Tom investigates his Native-American roots.
summaries.full: Tom rents a classic convertible car and meets Ally for lunch, where they get to know each other a little better. Bea and Pete arrive to share Tom's last two weeks in America. With the help of an American Indian chief and shaman, Tom investigates his Native-American roots. A phone call from Mr. Pfister in London, who has Tom's DNA results, tells him even more about his roots.

summaries.short: Tom participates in a Civil War re-enactment and learns about his great-great-grandfather's mysterious past.
summaries.full: Tom's cousin Rick, an American Civil War enthusiast, helps Tom find out more about his great-great-grandfather. A car accident leads Tom to meet a beautiful aspiring writer, Ally Keele, and the attraction appears to be mutual. Tom gamely participates in a Civil War re-enactment. Mid-battle, he gets some news from England.

summaries.short: Tom flies to the U.S. to bond with Al Chadwick and his American cousins.
summaries.full: Tom arrives in Los Angeles to stay with his American cousins, Al and Kitty Chadwick, and to try and discover why his great-great-grandfather Charles left for England more than a hundred years ago. Al has invited two other cousins--Rick, who also lives in California, and Dave, who's on a road trip from North Carolina--to a family barbecue.
